    "narrative": "The Austin Waves\u2019 offensive outlook for April 7, 2026, is headlined by **Gunnar Henderson** (81.17) and **Josh Lowe** (72.21), who represent the highest-upside plays in the lineup. **Gunnar Henderson** benefits from a massive 14% boost due to dynamic platoon advantages and, crucially, a slow-delivery opposing pitcher that significantly inflates his stolen base probability\u2014a priority for our 5x5 Roto strategy. Similarly, **Josh Lowe** and **Nolan Schanuel** (67.16) are positioned to feast on the weak 6.36 xERA of the opposing starter, with **Josh Lowe** seeing his score elevated by a combined 33% from SP skill and platoon favorability. Despite facing Gausman, **Kyle Tucker** remains an elite start (67.84) due to his consistent ability to command the zone and his favorable #2 spot in the order.\n\nThe most difficult decision on the bench was **Miguel Vargas** (49.69), who narrowly missed the cut behind the marginal output of **Jacob Wilson** (53.21) and **Jackson Merrill** (51.82). While **Miguel Vargas** offers solid base projections, the optimizer favored the higher volatility and potential for categorical contribution from our starters. We remain cautious regarding **Jackson Merrill** (51.82), as he faces the elite arm of Skenes, further hampered by the presence of a top-tier catcher behind the plate, which lowers his stolen base ceiling. **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.** (52.89) is also flagged for a difficult matchup against Yamamoto; his score is dragged down by a 16% reduction for the pitcher\u2019s elite skill, though his solid xwOBA keeps him in the starting nine for now. We continue to monitor **Jordan Westburg**\u2019s status on the IL, while keeping **Heliot Ramos**, **Coby Mayo**, and **Luis Garc\u00eda Jr.**, **Marcell Ozuna**, **Josh Jung**, and **Liam Hicks** on standby should defensive shifts or late-breaking lineup changes necessitate a pivot.",
